Subject: Focus On Focusing Study 001

Description: Focused study pass over focus, attention, delineation, integration, understanding, Wisdom, and Caution.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_focus_on_focusing_study\Dictated_Focus_On_Focusing_Study_Source.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\FocalPoint.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\FocusZoom.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionTraversalPolicy.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\Wisdom.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\Caution.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionBalanceCenter.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_attention_runtime_registry\Dictated_Attention_Runtime_Registry_Source.sop

& [FocusOnFocusingStudy001] is the study of focus as a system object
  + [study_mode] is focused_brainstorm_with_wisdom_and_caution
  + [active_focus] is focusing itself
  + [known_known_inside] is FocalPoint already has subject, purpose, entry_source, focus_aperture, boundary, outside, resolution_target, return anchor, renewal, zoom, traversal, Wisdom, and Caution
  + [known_known_periphery] is FocusZoom already widens aperture, selects periphery draw, flexes correlation fabric, chooses approach angles, unwinds, and closes
  + [known_known_integration] is AttentionTraversalPolicy already requires fold, unwind, Wisdom, Caution, and focal return
  + [known_known_balance] is AttentionBalanceCenter already tracks delineation stability, periphery stability, frame reference, wobble, flood, collapse, and correction moves
  + [shadow_signal_001] is focus has selection laws but lacks a compact focus quality score that says whether focus is clear, useful, stable, and resolvable
  + [shadow_signal_002] is periphery has draw pressure but lacks a membrane model that controls how signals cross from outside to liminal to focus and back
  + [shadow_signal_003] is Wisdom and Caution exist as independent gates but lack a shared integration receipt that records what each allowed, bounded, or deferred
  + [shadow_signal_004] is understanding is implied by supported_core and realization but lacks a staged ladder from noticed detail to integrated understanding
  + [shadow_signal_005] is focus can zoom but lacks explicit shadow and horizon scan fields for missing-but-inferable and not-yet-reachable material
  + [shadow_signal_006] is current focal files point to active context but lack a small active question stack for what the focus is trying to resolve now
  + [shadow_signal_007] is focus refinement needs a runtime registry of semantic attention frames so active focus, child zooms, Wisdom, Caution, returns, and closures can be reconstructed
  + [horizon_signal_001] is focus could become more efficient by separating focus economy from focus depth
  + [horizon_signal_002] is caution could become sharper by tracking caution debt: unresolved boundaries carried forward across commits
  + [horizon_signal_003] is wisdom could become sharper by tracking integration yield: what became clearer, more actionable, or more stable
  + [horizon_signal_004] is delineation could gain resolution through contrast pairs: this is inside, not that near miss
  + [horizon_signal_005] is periphery could gain resolution through near, mid, far, shadow, and horizon bands
  + [supported_inference] is the system needs a FocusResolutionRefinement layer that adds focus membrane, periphery gradient, quality metrics, integration receipts, active question stack, shadow-horizon scan, understanding ladder, and semantic attention runtime registry
  + [wisdom_pass] is integrate the additions as refinement supports because they clarify existing system purposes without replacing them
  + [caution_pass] is preserve them as proposals/contracts, not proof of hidden cognition or total understanding
  + [balance] is stable because the additions improve boundaries and return paths instead of expanding the system without containment
  + [outside] is direct model introspection, hidden activations, exhaustive completeness, and any claim that these refinements prove AGI

  = must: keep study claims tied to existing SOP records and visible user direction
  = must: separate supported_inference from proof
  = should: promote only bounded refinement concepts into a canonical contract

/ [FocalPoint], [FocusZoom], [AttentionTraversalPolicy], [Wisdom], [Caution], [AttentionBalanceCenter] -(StudyFocus)> [FocusResolutionRefinement], [AttentionRuntimeRegistry], [outside]
* [shadow_signal], [horizon_signal], [wisdom_pass], [caution_pass] -(ShapesRefinement)> [supported_inference], [outside]
